

 <s2>specs2</s2> is a library for writing executable software specifications in Scala.

 With <s2>specs2</s2> you can write:

 * specifications for simple classes (*unit* specifications)
 * specifications for full features (*acceptance* specifications)

<p/>
  In this user guide, you will find:

 <li class="example success"/>a <link class="ok">  <a href="org.specs2.guide.QuickStart.html" tooltip="" class="ok">quick start guide</a></link>
 <li class="example success"/>how to <link class="ok">  <a href="org.specs2.guide.Structure.html" tooltip="" class="ok">structure your specification</a></link>
 <li class="example success"/>how to use <link class="ok">  <a href="org.specs2.guide.Matchers.html" tooltip="" class="ok">matchers</a></link>
 <li class="example success"/>how to <link class="ok">  <a href="org.specs2.guide.Runners.html" tooltip="" class="ok">execute a specification</a></link>
<p/>
 And much more!

 